  <sharedSelectionEntryGroups>
    <selectionEntryGroup id="425b-e0c9-20b9-6018" name="Command Cards" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true">
      <selectionEntries>
        <selectionEntry id="0ec7-e5cf-0d3b-c8a4" name="Lucky" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
          <comment>added in v6 by willus8888</comment>
          <profiles>
            <profile id="be7d-5331-4839-ac58" name="Lucky" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
              <comment>added in v6 by willus8888</comment>
              <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Discard this card to re-roll any one die. The second result must be used.</characteristic>
                <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">Soviet, Force, Limited</characteristic>
                <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7"/>
              </characteristics>
            </profile>
          </profiles>
          <categoryLinks>
            <categoryLink id="bc91-907b-5845-40bd" name="Command Cards" hidden="false" targetId="c5b6-63ee-3f81-25f2" primary="true"/>
          </categoryLinks>
          <costs>
            <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="1.0"/>
          </costs>
        </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="af81-2bb2-1754-6237" name="UNSORTED" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
          <profiles>
            <profile id="0467-0d36-577d-6684" name="For Mother Russia" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
              <comment>added in v6 by willus8888</comment>
              <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Discard this card to have all Units in this Formation whose Unit Leader is within 6&quot;/15cm and in Line of Sight of the Formation Commander, automatically pass their Last Stand test for this turn.</characteristic>
                <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">Soviet, Formation, Limited</characteristic>
                <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7"/>
              </characteristics>
            </profile>
            <profile id="0be4-389b-9074-17f7" name="Molotov Cocktails" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
              <comment>added in v6 by willus8888</comment>
              <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Discard this card to give Infantry teams in the Unit Anti-tak 3 and Firepower 1+ against Top Armour in Assaults until the end of this turn.</characteristic>
                <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">Soviet, Unit (Infantry)</characteristic>
                <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7"/>
              </characteristics>
            </profile>
            <profile id="8624-0ebb-c574-c7d5" name="Hero Tankodesantniki" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
              <comment>added in v6 by willus8888</comment>
              <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">PPSh SMG teams from this Unit can Shoot while Mounted on Armoured Tank teams (to a maximum of one PPSh SMG team per Tank), and can Dismount when Charging into Contact.</characteristic>
                <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">Soviet, Build, Unit (Hero SMG Company), Limited</characteristic>
                <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7"/>
              </characteristics>
            </profile>
            <profile id="446c-a885-5569-d717" name="Softskin Transport" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
              <comment>added in v6 by willus8888</comment>
              <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">This Gun Unit may add a Softskin Tramsport Attachment.
The number of vehicles in the Unit is one Softskin Transport for each Team in the Unit.

Motivation
Confident 4+

Skill
Green 5+

Is Hit On
Reckless 2+

Save
Tank 5+

Tactical
-

Terrain Dash
8&quot;/20cm

Cross Country Dash
10&quot;/25cm

Road Dash
28&quot;/70cm

Cross
5+

Special Rules
Tractor: Team can carry one Gun Team as Passengers.

Softskin: If a Transport is Destroyed, any Passengers it is carrying are also Destroyed, and Unit immediately Dismounts and all of its Transports are Sent to the Rear.
All Passengers must Dismount from this Unit at the sametime. Empty Transport Teams must be Sent to the Rear.

Unarmoured: Team cannot Charge into Contact and must Break Off if Assaulted.</characteristic>
                <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">Soviet, Build, Unit (Gun)</characteristic>
                <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7"/>
              </characteristics>
            </profile>
            <profile id="73ea-fd71-aaf0-1279" name="Tankodesantniki" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
              <comment>added in v6 by willus8888</comment>
              <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">PPSh SMG teams from this Unit can Shoot while Mounted on Armoured Tank teams (to a maximum of one PPSh SMG team per Tank), and can Dismount when Charging into Contact.</characteristic>
                <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">Soviet, Build, Unit (SMG Company), Limited</characteristic>
                <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7"/>
              </characteristics>
            </profile>
          </profiles>
          <costs>
            <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
          </costs>
        </selectionEntry>
      </selectionEntries>
    </selectionEntryGroup>
  </sharedSelectionEntryGroups>
  <sharedRules>
    <rule id="5ea1-8955-1425-67f2" name="Flame-Thrower" page="" hidden="false">
      <description>Infantry, Gun, and Unarmoured Tank Teams re-roll successful Saves when hit by a Flame-thrower, and the Unit is automatically Pinned Down. Armoured Tank Teams use their Top armour for Armour Saves when hit by a Flame-thrower.

Flame-throwers may shoot in Defensive Fire. However, while a Unit that is Hit by a Flame-thrower is Pinned Down, this does not automatically stop the assault. The defender stil lneeds to score five (or eight) hits as normal to stop the assault.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="fe81-5b63-84e6-ea64" name="Kommisar" page="" hidden="false">
      <description>While their Kommisar team is In Command, a Unit has a better Motivation, as shown in the Kommisar column on the Unit Card.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="6010-01ce-a73f-5f10" name="Unit Transport" page="" hidden="false">
      <description>The Unit Leader of the Transport Attachment must end the Movement Step within 6”/15cm of the Unit Leader of its Passenger Unit while on table. If it cannot do this, then the Transport Attachment must be Sent to the Rear (see page 45 of the rulebook).</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="7ff9-516a-8b8c-1e6e" name="Urrah" page="" hidden="false">
      <description>Units with Urrah may move 6&quot;/15cm (instead of 4&quot;/10cm) when Charging into Contact.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="e94a-6edb-c9b2-2832" name="Salvo" page="" hidden="false">
      <description>Weapons with a ROF of &apos;Salvo&apos; are Artillery weapons and fire Artillery Bombardments, but use a 10&quot;/25cm square Salvo Template rather than the normal 6&quot;/15cm Artillery Template.

A Salvo Template may not be placed within 6&quot;/15cm of a friendly Team.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="881d-6680-3844-4af5" name="Little Tanks" page="" hidden="false">
      <description>In missions with Deep Reserves, you may only field one Tank Unit of Little Tanks, one Tank Unit with Front Armour of 3 or more, or one Aircraft Unit on the table at the start of the game.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="e367-9f4f-f7d0-8852" name="Redemption" page="" hidden="false">
      <description>When a Penal Unit is placed on the table during Deployment (but not if it is placed outside the normal Deployment Area using the Spearhead rule), the player may immediately Move its Teams at Tactical or Dash speed.
This movement may not use any Movement Orders, and may not take a Team within:
•	16&quot;/40cm of an enemy Team it is not Concealed from,
•	8&quot;/20cm of any enemy Team,
•	16&quot;/40cm of the enemy Deployment Area or any Objective outside your own Deployment Area.
A Penal Unit may not be placed in Reserve.
A Penal Unit never benefits from Bulletproof Cover.
A Penal Unit can prevent the enemy from Holding an Objective, but cannot Hold an Objective. Ignore a Destroyed Penal Unit when calculating Victory Points.
</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="7de2-8378-eb56-6a09" name="Sniper&apos;s Hide" page="" hidden="false">
      <description>Sniper Teams are always Gone to Ground.
Sniper Teams can be held in Ambush in addition to any other Teams permitted by the mission. If held in Reserve, they may still be placed from Ambush once they arrive on table.
When placed from Ambush, Sniper Teams may be placed in their own Deployment Area or in No Man&apos;s Land.
Teams from a Sniper Unit are separate Independent Teams rather than a Unit, and are ignored when determining wherther or not the Formation is In Good Spirits.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="874a-da0a-490c-1972" name="Unseen Killer" page="" hidden="false">
      <description>The target player cannot use the Mistaken Target rule if the Shooting Team is a Sniper Team.
If an Infantry, Gun, or Unarmoured Tank Team is hit by a Sniper Team, its Unit is Pinned Down.</description>
    </rule>
  </sharedRules>
